facts.seriesTitle: Maternal mortality ratio
facts.fact_text: The maternal mortality ratio decreased from 74 per 100,000 live births in 1990 to 15 per 100,000 live births in 2015.

facts.seriesTitle: Under-five mortality rate
facts.fact_text: The mortality rate of children under 5 years of age fell from 20 per 1,000 live births in 2000 to 7.8 per 1,000 live births in 2017.

facts.seriesTitle: Number of new HIV infections per 1,000 uninfected population
facts.fact_text: In 2017, there were about 0.03 people in every 100,000 uninfected population that became newly infected with HIV.

facts.seriesTitle: Participation rate in organized learning (one year before the official primary entry age)
facts.fact_text: In 2017, 95.95 % of children participated in pre-primary or primary education in the year prior to the official entrance age for primary school

facts.seriesTitle: Proportion of women aged 20-24 years who were married or in a union before age 18 (percent)
facts.fact_text: In 2009, 6.1 % of women between 20 to 24 years of age reported having been married before their eighteenth birthday

facts.seriesTitle: Proportion of seats held by women in national parliaments (percent)
facts.fact_text: The proportion of seats held by women in single or lower houses of parliament increased from 2.34 % in 2000 to 3.13% in 2018.

facts.seriesTitle: Proportion of population with access to electricity (percent)

facts.seriesTitle: Annual growth rate of real GDP per capita (percent)

facts.seriesTitle: Proportion of urban population living in slums (percent)

facts.seriesTitle: Annual mean levels of fine particulate matter in cities (micrograms per cubic meter)
facts.fact_text: In 2016, the annual population-weighted average mean concentration of fine suspended particles of less than 2.5 microns in diameter (PM2.5) was about 30.67 micrograms per cubic metre. This is above the maximum level for safety set by WHO of 10 micrograms per cubic metre.
